{"title": "Antichrist", "description": "Save for his raucous, rhapsodical autobiography, <i>Ecce Homo</i>, <i>The Antichrist</i> is the last thing that Nietzsche ever wrote, and so it may be accepted as a statement of some of his most salient ideas in their final form. Of all Nietzsche\u2019s books, <i>The Antichrist</i> comes nearest to conventionality in form. It presents a connected argument with very few interludes, and has a beginning, a middle and an end. The reason to listen to this version is that H.L. Mencken, the famous journalist, turned Nietzsche's German into such direct, plain-spoken American English that it puts the haranguing philosopher right up in your face.", "duration": 14277, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "411", "name": "Friedrich Nietzsche"}], "coverArt": "https://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt4/The_Antichrist_1005.jpg", "copyright_year": "1895", "genres": ["*Non-fiction", "Atheism & Agnosticism"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "ML Cohen"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Gesine"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Introduction by HL Mencken", "readers": [100], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/antichrist_librivox_/antichrist_01_nietzsche_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2366}, {"section": 2, "title": "Author's Preface", "readers": [128], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/antichrist_librivox_/antichrist_02_nietzsche_64kb.mp3", "duration": 194}, {"section": 3, "title": "1-19 (Christianity, Theology, Kant)", "readers": [613], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/antichrist_librivox_/antichrist_03_nietzsche_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2484}, {"section": 4, "title": "20-26 (Buddhism, Jews)", "readers": [56], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/antichrist_librivox_/antichrist_04_nietzsche_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1558}, {"section": 5, "title": "27-42 (Jesus)", "readers": [100], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/antichrist_l